cienaWsSystemMIB.name: cienaWsSystemMIB

revisions.description: Waveserver Release 1.5 Obsolete: leaf 'user-message-state' in 'front-display'. Obsolete: leaf 'reset-to-factory-default-button' in container 'global-provisioning'. Added scp server support. Added 'chassis-functionality' attribute.

Waveserver Rel 1.4 revision. Added containers and leaf: environment/root/password. Obsolete: leaf lamp-test in container global-provisioning. Added container lamp-flash-test and RPCs ws-system-enable-lamp-mode and ws-system-disable-lamp-mode. Aligned MIB files to respect YANG read/write status.
Waveserver Rel 1.3 revised. Change the fraction-digits for leaf time-offset from 5 to 2.
Waveserver Rel 1.2 revised. Major restructuring of this YANG module.

Waveserver Rel 1.1 revised. enum value updated for leaves: sftp-server-state, web-server-state, netconf-server-state, restconf-server-state, zero-touch-provisioning-admin, low-power-mode, display-admin-state, display-screensaver-state, display-user-message-state, display-input-button, lamp-test

cienaWsSystemMIB.description: This YANG module defines Ciena's WaveServer System representation for the NETCONF protocol

cwsSystemSiteId.name: cwsSystemSiteId
cwsSystemSiteId.description: An integer to uniquely identify the site where this Waveserver is located. This is used to help group Waveservers together with line system equipment. All equipment in a common site should share the same site identifier.

cwsSystemSiteName.name: cwsSystemSiteName
cwsSystemSiteName.description: The name for the site where the Waveserver is located.

cwsSystemSiteLatitude.name: cwsSystemSiteLatitude
cwsSystemSiteLatitude.description: Geographic coordinate for the site location in degrees.

cwsSystemSiteLongitude.name: cwsSystemSiteLongitude
cwsSystemSiteLongitude.description: Geographic coordinate for the site location in degrees.

cwsSystemSiteAddress.name: cwsSystemSiteAddress
cwsSystemSiteAddress.description: The street address of the site.

cwsSystemGroupId.name: cwsSystemGroupId
cwsSystemGroupId.description: An integer to uniquely identify a group of Waveservers within a site.

cwsSystemGroupName.name: cwsSystemGroupName
cwsSystemGroupName.description: A name for the group of Waveservers.

cwsSystemGroupDescription.name: cwsSystemGroupDescription
cwsSystemGroupDescription.description: A description for the group of Waveservers.

cwsSystemMemberId.name: cwsSystemMemberId
cwsSystemMemberId.description: An integer to uniquely identify a Waveserver chassis within a group of Waveservers. Initial configuration of this identifier automatically assigns 2 specific wavelengths for the Ciena wavelength grid to the Wavelogic 3 Extreme ports 1 and 12. Wavelengths can also be manually assigned independently.

cwsSystemMemberName.name: cwsSystemMemberName
cwsSystemMemberName.description: A name for the Waveserver chassis.

cwsSystemMemberDescription.name: cwsSystemMemberDescription
cwsSystemMemberDescription.description: A description for the Waveserver chassis.

cwsSystemMemberFrameIdentification.name: cwsSystemMemberFrameIdentification
cwsSystemMemberFrameIdentification.description: A description to identify the location of the Waveserver chassis within the data center. For example, the building, floor, aisle, frame number, etc.

cwsSystemMemberRackUnitNumber.name: cwsSystemMemberRackUnitNumber
cwsSystemMemberRackUnitNumber.description: A logical identifier for the Waveservers location within the frame or rack. For example, the device at the top could be labelled unit 1.

cwsSystemTimeConfigDate.name: cwsSystemTimeConfigDate
cwsSystemTimeConfigDate.description: Date: must be in format: yyyy-mm-dd, or yy-mm-dd, or mm-dd.

cwsSystemTimeConfigTime.name: cwsSystemTimeConfigTime
cwsSystemTimeConfigTime.description: Time: must be in format: hh:mm:ss

cwsSystemTimeConfigTimeOffset.name: cwsSystemTimeConfigTimeOffset
cwsSystemTimeConfigTimeOffset.description: System time-offset from UTC in seconds.

cwsSystemTimeConfigTimeStamp.name: cwsSystemTimeConfigTimeStamp
cwsSystemTimeConfigTimeStamp.description: System time stamp format: local time or UTC time.

cwsSystemTimeConfigSystemUptime.name: cwsSystemTimeConfigSystemUptime
cwsSystemTimeConfigSystemUptime.description: Time since last reboot, in format: xxxd xxh xxm xxs

cwsSystemServerConfigSftpServerState.name: cwsSystemServerConfigSftpServerState
cwsSystemServerConfigSftpServerState.description: Indicate whether SFTP server is enabled.

cwsSystemServerConfigWebServerState.name: cwsSystemServerConfigWebServerState
cwsSystemServerConfigWebServerState.description: Indicate whether web server is enabled, HTTPS only.

cwsSystemServerConfigNetconfServerState.name: cwsSystemServerConfigNetconfServerState
cwsSystemServerConfigNetconfServerState.description: Indicate whether netconf server is enabled.

cwsSystemServerConfigRestconfServerState.name: cwsSystemServerConfigRestconfServerState
cwsSystemServerConfigRestconfServerState.description: Indicate whether RESTCONF server is enabled, HTTPS only.

cwsSystemXftpConfigMode.name: cwsSystemXftpConfigMode
cwsSystemXftpConfigMode.description: XFTP mode: FTP, SFTP, or TFTP

cwsSystemTftpConfigHostName.name: cwsSystemTftpConfigHostName
cwsSystemTftpConfigHostName.description: TFTP host name configured by user.

cwsSystemFtpHostName.name: cwsSystemFtpHostName
cwsSystemFtpHostName.description: FTP host name configured by user.

cwsSystemSftpHostName.name: cwsSystemSftpHostName
cwsSystemSftpHostName.description: SFTP host name configured by user.

cwsSystemScpHostName.name: cwsSystemScpHostName
cwsSystemScpHostName.description: SCP host name configured by user.

cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningLowPowerMode.name: cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningLowPowerMode
cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningLowPowerMode.description: Low power mode is enabled or disabled

cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningLampTest.name: cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningLampTest
cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningLampTest.description: Enable to initiate chassis level lamp test. Disable to end the test.

cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningResetToFactor.name: cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningResetToFactoryDefaultButton
cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningResetToFactor.description: Indicate whether the reset button for reset to factory default is enabled. If enabled, the reset button on the faceplate will trigger a reset to factory default settings

cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningChassisFuncti.name: cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningChassisFunctionality
cwsSystemGlobalProvisioningChassisFuncti.description: Description of chassis functionality, used by MCP.

cwsSystemFrontDisplayAdminState.name: cwsSystemFrontDisplayAdminState
cwsSystemFrontDisplayAdminState.description: Display is enabled or disabled. When the display is disabled, it will be turned off and will not be woken up by pressing on the faceplate navigation buttons

cwsSystemFrontDisplayScreensaverState.name: cwsSystemFrontDisplayScreensaverState
cwsSystemFrontDisplayScreensaverState.description: Screensaver is enabled or disabled. When the screensaver is enabled, the LED display on the faceplate will be automatically turned off after N minutes of inactivity. If an input button is pressed, it will turn the display back on. The length of the screensaver idle time is controlled by the screensaver-timeout parameter.

cwsSystemFrontDisplayScreensaverTimeout.name: cwsSystemFrontDisplayScreensaverTimeout
cwsSystemFrontDisplayScreensaverTimeout.description: Number of minutes before screensaver activates. The screensaver can be disabled via the display-screensaver-state attribute. The display can be completely disabled via the display-admin-state attribute.

cwsSystemFrontDisplayInputButtonState.name: cwsSystemFrontDisplayInputButtonState
cwsSystemFrontDisplayInputButtonState.description: Enable or disable display input control.

cwsSystemFrontDisplayUserMessageState.name: cwsSystemFrontDisplayUserMessageState
cwsSystemFrontDisplayUserMessageState.description: Enable or disable user message display. If a user-message has been provisioned, enabling it via this parameter will display that message on the LED display. This leaf is now obsolete in WS 1.5

cwsSystemFrontDisplayUserMessage.name: cwsSystemFrontDisplayUserMessage
cwsSystemFrontDisplayUserMessage.description: Message to be shown on the display. This is a custom message to be displayed on the LED display.

cwsSystemLineConfigBandPlan.name: cwsSystemLineConfigBandPlan
cwsSystemLineConfigBandPlan.description: Band Plan. The band plan is a way of selecting a mapping between channels and wavelengths/frequencies. The selected band plan should correspond to the band plan on the line system. The band plan is used to automatically select the next wavelength or frequency for newly installed Waveservers based on the member-id assigned to the device. Modifying Band plan will have an effect on PTP attributes. Software will automatically assign a per-defined PTP Wavelength, Frequency, and Channel combination from selected Band Plan. Note that the automatic reassignment will only occur when a valid Band Plan is already provisioned (i.e. existing Band Plan is not equal to None), the existing PTP Wavelength, Frequency, and Channel have value of zero, and user provisions Member ID from 0 to a non-zero value (i.e. from 'uncommisioned' state to 'commissioned' state) that's within the maximum wavelength allocation specified in the Band Plan (each Member ID reserves two wavelengths) . Software shall automatically update existing channel number provisioning when user changes Band Plan provisioning. Channel number shall be set to 0 if provisioned wavelength/frequency is not found in the new Band Plan or the new Band Plan equals to None.

cwsSystemLineConfigLineProtection.name: cwsSystemLineConfigLineProtection
cwsSystemLineConfigLineProtection.description: Line protection settings. If line protection is enabled, this means that the photonic line the Waveserver is connected to has protection enabled. In the event of a line side fault, the protection card on the line side will select the protection path and the modems will reacquire the signal on the alternate path. While the switch is occuring, link state messaging will be disabled to the clients so that the connected devices do not attempt a switch or a restoration.

cwsSystemLampFlashTestOperationalState.name: cwsSystemLampFlashTestOperationalState
cwsSystemLampFlashTestOperationalState.description: Lamp flash test operational state. It reflects whether the lamp flash test is enabled or disabled.

cwsSystemLampFlashTestMode.name: cwsSystemLampFlashTestMode
cwsSystemLampFlashTestMode.description: Lamp mode selection. The default mode is flash. It is the only mode supported

cwsSystemLampFlashTestTargetType.name: cwsSystemLampFlashTestTargetType
cwsSystemLampFlashTestTargetType.description: Lamp testing target type. It can be chassis or port. The default type is chassis. When the target-type is port, the port list should be set for the selected ports to be tested.

cwsSystemLampFlashTestTimeout.name: cwsSystemLampFlashTestTimeout
cwsSystemLampFlashTestTimeout.description: The number of minutes the lamp flash testing will be operating when enabled. The default timeout value is 30 minutes

cwsSystemLampFlashTestPorts.name: cwsSystemLampFlashTestPorts
cwsSystemLampFlashTestPorts.description: Ports selected for lamp flash test. The bits in this leaf represent port number from 1 to 12, starting from position 1. When target-type is port and lamp-flash-test is enabled, the selected ports (bit is set) will have its lamp operate in the mode set. When the target-type is chassis, this leaf should not be specified or should be empty.
